<refentry xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"
          xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
          xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
          xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"
          xmlns:db="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"
          version="5.0-subset Scilab"
          xml:id="XcosMenuEval">
  <refnamediv>
    <refname>Eval</refname>
    <refpurpose>Menu: (re)-evaluate the Scicos block parameters</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  <refsection>
    <title>Description</title>
    <para>
      Block parameters may be Scilab instructions.  They are evaluated
      immediately when set but the entered expressions are also stored
      as character strings (see the <literal>exprs</literal> field in
      the <link linkend="scicos_graphics">scicos_graphics</link> data
      structure).
    </para>
    <para> 
      Select this menu item to have them re-evaluated according to new
      values of <link linkend="XcosMenuContext">Scicos context</link> or
      Scilab variables.
    </para>
    <para> 
      When a formal variable definition is changed in the <link
      linkend="XcosMenuContext">Scicos context</link> the parameters of each
      bloks are automatically re-evaluated, so the
      <literal>Eval</literal> menu has only to be used in special
      cases (use of variables defined in the Scilab environment, ...)

    </para>
  </refsection>
  <refsection>
    <title>See Also</title>
    <simplelist type="inline">
      <member> <link linkend="XcosMenuContext">Context</link> </member>
      <member> <link linkend="scicos_graphics">scicos_graphics</link> </member>
     </simplelist>
   </refsection>
</refentry>
